 These three above charts illustrate the alpha diversity present across the different sample sites. Overall, all the JGI sample sites showed significantly higher levels of diversity for the raw observations as well as the Fisher index; however, when entropy is taken into account with shannon diversity, the gap narrows, and the standard (Uren) and JGI primer datasets are closer to one another. the JGI still has somewhat higher diversity, though. Additionally, while the JGI species counts are more variable for the results of the Observed and Fisher values, they show less variability in Shannon entropy. The inverse is seen with results from the standard primer set. 
 
 
